President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 8, 2013, as National Grandparents Day in the United States. In the proclamation, he acknowledges the significant role grandparents play in society as caregivers, teachers, and sources of wisdom. He emphasizes the contributions made by previous generations in shaping the country and calls on Americans to honor their own grandparents and those in their community. The proclamation highlights the need to provide care and support for grandparents in their golden years.